ed when <code>enabled</code> is\\n         <code>true</code>.</p>\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"startDelayInMilliseconds\": {","+          \"target\": \"com.amazonaws.lexmodelsv2#AudioFillerDelayInMilliseconds\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#documentation\": \"<p>The time, in milliseconds, to wait after the end of the user's\\n         utterance before starting audio filler playback. Valid range is\\n         <code>500</code> to <code>5000</code> milliseconds. If not specified,\\n         Amazon Lex uses a default of <code>2500</code> milliseconds.</p>\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"minimumPlayDurationInMilliseconds\": {","+          \"target\": \"com.amazonaws.lexmodelsv2#AudioFillerDurationInMilliseconds\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#documentation\": \"<p>The minimum time, in milliseconds, that audio filler plays once it\\n         has started, even if the bot response becomes ready sooner. Valid range\\n         is <code>1000</code> to <code>5000</code> milliseconds. If not\\n         specified, Amazon Lex uses a default of <code>3000</code>\\n         milliseconds.</p>\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"responseDeliveryDelayInMilliseconds\": {","+          \"target\": \"com.amazonaws.lexmodelsv2#AudioFillerDeliveryDelayInMilliseconds\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#documentation\": \"<p>The silent delay, in milliseconds, inserted between the end of audio\\n         filler playback and the start of the bot's response. Valid range is\\n         <code>200</code> to <code>1000</code> milliseconds. If not specified,\\n         Amazon Lex uses a default of <code>500</code> milliseconds.</p>\"","+          }","+        }","+      },","+      \"traits\": {","+        \"smithy.api#documentation\": \"<p>Configuration that plays background filler audio during speech-to-speech\\n         interactions to mask processing delays and improve the perceived\\n         responsiveness of the bot.</p>\\n         <p>Audio filler requires <code>unifiedSpeechSettings</code> (speech-to-speech)\\n         to be enabled on the bot locale when <code>enabled</code> is\\n         <code>true</code>.</p>\"","+      }","+    },","+    \"com.amazonaws.lexmodelsv2#AudioFillerType\": {","+      \"type\": \"enum\",","+      \"members\": {","+        \"MELODY_CHIPPER_CHIME\": {","+          \"target\": \"smithy.api#Unit\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#enumValue\": \"MELODY_CHIPPER_CHIME\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"MELODY_CURIOUS_CRAWL\": {","+          \"target\": \"smithy.api#Unit\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#enumValue\": \"MELODY_CURIOUS_CRAWL\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"MELODY_RISING_RIPPLE\": {","+          \"target\": \"smithy.api#Unit\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#enumValue\": \"MELODY_RISING_RIPPLE\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"MELODY_PATIENT_PING\": {","+          \"target\": \"smithy.api#Unit\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#enumValue\": \"MELODY_PATIENT_PING\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"MELODY_PONDERING_PONG\": {","+          \"target\": \"smithy.api#Unit\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#enumValue\": \"MELODY_PONDERING_PONG\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"TYPING_KINETIC_KEYS\": {","+          \"target\": \"smithy.api#Unit\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#enumValue\": \"TYPING_KINETIC_KEYS\"","+          }","+        },","+        \"TYPING_QUIET_QWERTY\": {","+          \"target\": \"smithy.api#Unit\",","+          \"traits\": {","+            \"smithy.api#enumValue\": \"TYPING_QUIET_QWERTY\"","+          }","+        }","+      },","+      \"traits\": {","+        \"smithy.api#documentation\": \"<p>The audio filler identifier played during speech-to-speech\\n         interactions. Supported values include melody and typing variants such\\n         as <code>MELODY_CHIPPER_CHIME</code>, <code>MELODY_CURIOUS_CRAWL</code>,\\n         <code>MELODY_RISING_RIPPLE</code>, <code>MELODY_PATIENT_PING</code>,\\n         <code>MELODY_PONDERING_PONG</code>, <code>TYPING_KINETIC_KEYS</code>,\\n         and <code>TYPING_QUIET_QWERTY</code>.</p>\","],"additions":96,"deletions":0,"truncated":false}],"additions":322,"deletions":34,"truncated":true,"file_count":12},"error":null,"fetched_at":"2026-05-20T17:48:16.798639+00:00"}